Improve Your Einstein Segment Creation Results in Data Cloud

What happens if you receive unclear results, or if the results aren’t necessarily what you’re hoping for? Use these suggestions to gain more accurate results.

Available with add-on license: Segmentation and Activation
Make your prompt specific to your brand

Include terms that you use to describe your brand that might not be common for others outside of your company. For example, if you use a specific customer type, specify this in your prompt, such as “all members who are customer type= NSH”. If you want to include a specific product or website, specify this in your prompt, for example, “customers who engaged with website= “mywesite.com.”

Check whether your prompt is ignoring specific fields

If specific fields are being ignored, try using more brand-specific terms or prepositions to simplify the prompt.

Remove unwanted attributes

If your results contain attributes that you don’t need or want, deselect them so that they aren’t included with your segment.

Use descriptive terms

If you need specific information, use descriptive terms in your prompt. For example, if you want data about active users, specify this in your prompt: “active users who engaged today.”

Broaden your search to increase your population count

If you receive a message that your result will produce a small population, try to broaden your search and focus on the data that you know exists.
